item.title: Technology Sep 6, 2025 Europe bets on Supercomputer Jupiter to takes on China and the US in AI, and do what it has NEVER been able to do so far Europe aims to close the AI gap with the United States and China by unveiling Jupiter, its first exascale supercomputer. Located in Germany, Jupiter boasts immense processing power for AI training, climate forecasting, and brain research. Despite relying on U.S.-made chips, this project signifies Europe's commitment to sovereign computing and economic competitiveness, with applications extending to clean energy optimization.

Located in Germany, Jupiter boasts immense processing power for AI training, climate forecasting, and brain research. Despite relying on U.S.-made chips, this project signifies Europe's commitment to sovereign computing and economic competitiveness, with applications extending to clean energy optimization.

Experts see Jupiter as a significant step for Europe in the AI sector, where it has lagged behind the US and China.

‘We have apologised to…’: Australia’s biggest bank decides not to replace human jobs with AI
The Commonwealth Bank of Australia (CBA) has backtracked on its plan to eliminate 45 customer service positions due to AI implementation, following pressure from the Finance Sector Union.
CBA admitted its assessment was flawed and offered affected employees options to remain, apply elsewhere, or exit.
